input: Triage incoming tickets, auto-fix common issues, escalate complex cases to engineers, and track resolution metrics.

inputs.name: K
inputs.input_data: Structured records mapping issue patterns to fixes

steps:
Uses: Incoming Tickets
Action: Retrieve raw ticket records from ticketing system API
Produces: Raw ticket dataset
Stores/Sends To: Processing queue

Uses: Escalation Criteria Threshold, Incoming Tickets
Action: Apply ML classifier to score ticket complexity against threshold
Produces: Ticket Classification (Common/Complex)
Stores/Sends To: Classification cache

Uses: Ticket Classification (Common/Complex), Auto-Fixable Issues List
Action: Match common tickets to knowledge base solutions and execute fixes

Uses: Ticket Classification (Common/Complex), On-Call Engineer Schedule
Action: Route complex tickets to appropriate engineers via escalation paths

Stores/Sends To: Engineering team communication channel

Uses: Auto-Fixed Tickets, Escalated Tickets Queue
Action: Aggregate resolution timestamps and success metrics
Produces: Metrics dataset
Stores/Sends To: Dashboard database

Uses: Metrics Dataset
Action: Update visualization components on metrics dashboard
Produces: Updated metrics dashboard
Stores/Sends To: Internal analytics platform
execution_plan.raw_response:
Inputs:
1. Incoming Tickets
   Source Type: SYSTEM-RETRIEVABLE
   Source Origin: Ticketing system API (e.g., Zendesk/Jira)
   Input Data: Raw ticket records with content, timestamps, priority
   Bound Reference: None

2. Knowledge Base of Common Solutions
   Source Type: SYSTEM-RETRIEVABLE
   Source Origin: Internal solutions database (e.g., Confluence/MySQL)
   Input Data: Structured records mapping issue patterns to fixes
   Bound Reference: None

3. Escalation Criteria Threshold
   Source Type: USER-CONTROLLED
   Source Origin: Operations team
   Input Data: Numeric complexity score threshold (e.g., >7/10)
   Note: Requires explicit user provision or linkage.

4. On-Call Engineer Schedule
   Source Type: SYSTEM-RETRIEVABLE
   Source Origin: Scheduling tool API (e.g., PagerDuty)
   Input Data: Current engineer availability and escalation paths
   Bound Reference: None

5. Ticket Classification (Common/Complex)
   Source Type: DERIVABLE
   Source Origin: Derived from Incoming Tickets + Escalation Criteria
   Input Data: Classification results per ticket
   Bound Reference: Input 1 & 3
   Note: [DEPTH STOP - Terminal input, do not further decompose]

6. Auto-Fixable Issues List
   Source Type: DERIVABLE
   Source Origin: Derived from Knowledge Base
   Input Data: Subset of knowledge base entries applicable to current tickets
   Bound Reference: Input 2
   Note: [DEPTH STOP - Terminal input, do not further decompose]

Outputs:
1. Auto-Fixed Tickets
2. Escalated Tickets Queue
3. Updated Metrics Dashboard
4. System Logs

Steps:
Step 1:
Uses: Incoming Tickets
Action: Retrieve raw ticket records from ticketing system API
Produces: Raw ticket dataset
Stores/Sends To: Processing queue

Step 2:
Uses: Escalation Criteria Threshold, Incoming Tickets
Action: Apply ML classifier to score ticket complexity against threshold
Produces: Ticket Classification (Common/Complex)
Stores/Sends To: Classification cache

Step 3:
Uses: Ticket Classification (Common/Complex), Auto-Fixable Issues List
Action: Match common tickets to knowledge base solutions and execute fixes
Produces: Auto-fixed tickets with resolution details
Stores/Sends To: Ticketing system API (status updates)

Step 4:
Uses: Ticket Classification (Common/Complex), On-Call Engineer Schedule
Action: Route complex tickets to appropriate engineers via escalation paths
Produces: Escalated tickets queue
Stores/Sends To: Engineering team communication channel

Step 5:
Uses: Auto-Fixed Tickets, Escalated Tickets Queue
Action: Aggregate resolution timestamps and success metrics
Produces: Metrics dataset
Stores/Sends To: Dashboard database

Step 6:
Uses: Metrics Dataset
Action: Update visualization components on metrics dashboard
Produces: Updated metrics dashboard
Stores/Sends To: Internal analytics platform
